174	  flowing through server-side blinding and a rater interface, splitting
175	  into domain-expert and end-user rating paths that merge into a
176	  validated submission. Panel B shows a DynamoDB evaluation record
177	  flowing through flat export, which fans out into four downstream
178	  products: aggregate analysis, a preferred-SFT set, preference pairs,
179	  and safety filtering.}
180	  \label{fig:workflow}
181	  \vspace{-2pt}
182	\end{figure*}
183	
184	Figure~\ref{fig:workflow} summarizes the collection and export
185	workflow. Rater Bench uses fixed benchmark bundles: each item contains
186	a rehabilitation question and exactly three model-generated candidate
187	answers, none manually authored. All three conditions are built on
188	GPT-4.1 mini but differ in context and tool access
189	(Table~\ref{tab:conditions}). The benchmark uses four question
190	categories (Table~\ref{tab:question_categories}), and each rater sees a
191	cohort-specific rubric (Table~\ref{tab:rubric-definitions}).
